cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper is about cooperative pathfinding in distributed systems with limited sensing and communication range, which involves multi-agent systems and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses the implementation and evaluation of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The approach involves planning and decision-making, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with coordination and communication between robots, which is relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the formal analysis of the approach, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
